other_tests.findings: Deletion of two nucleotides (delTT140) at codon 140 of exon 5 in the GNAS gene.

other_tests.date: At age 4 years and at age 7 years
other_tests.findings: At age 4, TSH level was 5.66 mU/mL; at age 7, TSH level was 4.40 mIU/mL despite levothyroxine treatment.
other_tests.changes_over_time: TSH levels remained at the upper limit of the normal range.

other_tests.findings: Post-transplantation, calcium, phosphate, and PTH levels rapidly normalized.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Within 1 year of transplantation, vitamin D supplements could be tapered; 4 months after discontinuation, PTH level was 23 pg/mL.
